				<tr>
					<td valign="top" nowrap class="usage"><p class="literal"></p>
					</td><td valign="top" nowrap class="requirements">H&eacute;rit&eacute;: oui</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="description"><p>Pour les feuilles de style audio, cet attribut d&eacute;finit la gamme dynamique (volume) des &eacute;l&eacute;ments parl&eacute;s. La parole normale comportant des inflexions qui rendent impossible l'utilisation permanente d'un volume absolu, l'attribut volume permet de d&eacute;finir le volume m&eacute;dian.</p>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="CLEARSEPARATION">&#160;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="csssyntax"><span class="title">Syntaxe CSS</span></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="CLEARSEPARATION">&#160;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><span class="programlisting"><pre>volume: <span class="replaceable">number</span>  | <span class="replaceable">percentage</span>  | <span class="replaceable">volumeConstant</span></pre>
						</span></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="CLEARSEPARATION">&#160;</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" colspan="2" class="value"><span class="title">Valeur</span></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><p>Un nombre (<span class="replaceable">number</span>) quelconque repr&eacute;sentant le volume souhait&eacute;. Z&eacute;ro repr&eacute;sente le volume minimum de son pour le mat&eacute;riel utilis&eacute; et l'environnement sonore ambiant, <span class="literal">100</span> repr&eacute;sente le volume maximum dans les m&ecirc;mes conditions. Si vous sp&eacute;cifiez un pourcentage (<span class="replaceable">percentage</span>), celui-ci est calcul&eacute; par rapport &agrave; l'attribut volume de l'&eacute;l&eacute;ment parent. Vous disposez &eacute;galement des constantes suivantes (correspondant &agrave; des volumes pr&eacute;d&eacute;finis): <span class="literal">silent</span> (aucun son) | <span class="literal">x-soft</span> (0) | <span class="literal">soft</span> (25) | <span class="literal">medium</span> (50) | <span class="literal">loud</span> (75) | <span class="literal">x-loud</span> (100).</p>
					</td>
				</tr>
